A young tree is a tree used in the Hunter skill when catching swamp lizards and salamanders. The player must construct a trap using one rope and one small fishing net. Adding bait to the trap will increase the odds of a successful catch. Different salamanders prefer different types of tar as bait. Players may dismantle the trap by right-clicking the tree and selecting "Dismantle".

Once the player has caught a their target, check the trap to receive the reward.

Locations[edit | edit source]

  • Swamp lizards are found in the hunting area south-east of the bank in Canifis.
  • Orange salamanders are found in the Uzer hunting area, south-west of the Ruins.
  • Red salamanders are found south-west of Ardougne, west of the Khazard Battlefield.
  • Black salamanders are found in level 20 Wilderness, north-east of the Chaos Temple.

A '''young tree''' is a tree used in the [[Hunter]] [[skill]] when catching [[swamp lizard]]s and [[salamander]]s. The player must construct a trap using one [[rope]] and one [[small fishing net]]. Adding bait to the trap will increase the odds of a successful catch. Different salamanders prefer different types of [[tar]] as bait. Players may dismantle the trap by right-clicking the tree and selecting "Dismantle".

Once the player has caught a their target, check the trap to receive the reward.

==Locations==
*[[Swamp lizard]]s are found in the hunting area south-east of the bank in [[Canifis]].
*[[Orange salamander]]s are found in the Uzer hunting area, south-west of the [[Ruins of Uzer|Ruins]].
*[[Red salamander]]s are found south-west of Ardougne, west of the [[Khazard Battlefield]].
*[[Black salamander]]s are found in level 20 Wilderness, north-east of the [[Chaos Temple (Wilderness)|Chaos Temple]].
